2013 Carl August von Groddeck\n*1863\u20131891 \u2013 Leopold von Winter\n*1891\u20131896 \u2013 Dr. Karl Adolf Baumbach\n*1896\u20131902 \u2013 Dr. [[Clemens von Delbr\u00fcck]]\n*1903\u20131910 \u2013 [https://de.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Heinrich_Otto_Ehlers&stable=1 Heinrich Otto Ehlers]\n*1910\u20131919 \u2013 Heinrich Heinrich Scholtz\n\n===[[Free City of Danzig]]===\n:''Free City of Danzig created by the [[Treaty of Versailles]]''\n[[File:Senate of the Free City of Danzig.JPG|thumb|right|Senate of the Free City of Danzig]]\n*1920\u20131931 \u2013 Dr. [[Heinrich Sahm]] (since 1920 President of Senate)\n*1931\u20131933 \u2013 [[Ernst Ziehm]] (President of Senate)\n*1933\u20131934 \u2013 [[Hermann Rauschning]] (President of Senate)\n*1934\u20131939 \u2013 [[Arthur Greiser]] (President of Senate)\n*1939 \u2013 [[Albert Forster]] (Head of State)\n\n===[[World War II]]===\n:''Free City occupied by [[Nazi Germany]] and incorporated into the [[Reichsgau Danzig-West Prussia]]''\n\n*1939\u20131945 \u2013 {{ill|Georg Lippke|de}}\n\n===[[Poland]]===\n:''Danzig conquered by [[Soviet Union]] in 1945 (see [[East Pomeranian Offensive]] and [[:ru:\u0412\u0437\u044f\u0442\u0438\u0435 \u0414\u0430\u043d\u0446\u0438\u0433\u0430 (1945)]]) and put under Polish administration, as Gda\u0144sk after the end of the World War II (see [[Recovered Territories]], [[Territorial changes of Poland immediately after World War II]] and [[Former eastern territories of Germany]] for details)''\n\n==See also==\n*[[List of mayors of Gda\u0144sk]] (1945\u2013present)\n*[[History of Gda\u0144sk]]\n**[[Timeline of Gda\u0144sk]]\n\n==External links==\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20071110222029/http://roots.gdansk.pl/en/postacie/burmistrzowie.php List at roots.gdansk.pl]\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:List Of Mayors Of Danzig}}\n[[Category:People from Gda\u0144sk|Mayors]]\n[[Category:History of Gda\u0144sk]]\n[[Category:Lists of mayors of places in Germany|Danzig]]\n[[Category:Lists of people by city|Danzig]]\n[[Category:Gda\u0144sk-related lists|Mayors]]\n", "name_user": "LimaMario", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eKingdom of Prussia and German Empire:{{ill}}", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_mayors_of_Danzig"}
{"title_page": "I Gotta Feeling", "text_new": "{{short description|2009 single by The Black Eyed Peas}}\n{{About|The Black Eyed Peas song|The Four Tops song|I Got a Feeling|The Beatles song|I've Got a Feeling|the Billy Currington song|I Got a Feelin'}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=April 2012}}\n{{Infobox song\n| name       = I Gotta Feeling\n| cover      = I Gotta Feeling.png\n| alt        =\n| type       = single\n| artist     = [[The Black Eyed Peas]]\n| album      = [[The E.N.D.]]\n| released   = {{Start date|2009|5|21|mf=y}}\n| format     = {{hlist|[[Gramophone record|7\"]]|[[CD single|CD]]|[[Music download|digital download]]}}\n| recorded   = 2009; Square Prod, Paris, France and Metropolis Studios, London, England\n| studio     =\n| venue      =\n| genre      = [[Dance-pop]]<ref>http://www.allmusic.com/album/the-end-energy-never-dies-mw0000813151</ref>\n| length     = {{ubl|4:50 {{small|(album version)}}|4:05 {{small|(radio edit)}}}}\n| label      = [[Interscope Records|Interscope]]\n| writer     = {{hlist|[[will.i.am|William Adams]]|[[Fergie (singer)|Stacy Ferguson]]|[[Taboo (rapper)|Jamie Gomez]]|[[David Guetta]]|[[apl.de.ap|Allan Pineda]]|Fr\u00e9d\u00e9ric Riesterer}}\n| producer   = {{hlist|[[David Guetta]]|Fr\u00e9d\u00e9ric Riesterer}}\n| prev_title = [[Boom Boom Pow]]\n| prev_year  = 2009\n| next_title = [[Meet Me Halfway]]\n| next_year  = 2009\n| misc       = {{External music video|1={{YouTube|uSD4vsh1zDA|\"I Gotta Feeling\"}} }}\n}}\n\n\"'''I Gotta Feeling'''\" is the second single from [[The Black Eyed Peas]]' fifth album ''[[The E.N.D.]]'', produced by French DJ [[David Guetta]].<ref>[https://www.theguardian.com/music/2009/jun/01/david-guetta-dance-music David Guetta: the man taking dance music into the US charts] \u2013 ''The Guardian''</ref> The song was released on May 21, 2009<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.femalefirst.co.uk/music/features/A+Decade+In+Music+2009+Song+Of+The+Year+I+Gotta+Feeling+Black+Eyed+Peas-10129.html|title=A Decade In Music 2009: Song Of The Year - I Gotta Feeling Black Eyed Peas|last=January 2010|first=4|website=www.femalefirst.co.uk|language=en|access-date=2019-08-14}}</ref> and debuted at number two on the Canadian and ''Billboard'' Hot 100, behind the group's \"[[Boom Boom Pow]]\", making the group one of 11 artists who have occupied the top two positions of the ''Billboard'' Hot 100 at the same time. It reached number one on the US charts and 20 charts worldwide.\n\nThe song was nominated for [[Grammy Award for Record of the Year|Record of the Year]] at the [[52nd Grammy Awards]] and won the [[Grammy Award|Grammy]] for [[Grammy Award for Best Pop Performance by a Duo or Group with Vocals|Best Pop Performance by a Duo or Group with Vocals]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.grammy.com/nominees |title=54th Annual GRAMMY Awards Nominees And Winners |publisher=GRAMMY.com |date= |access-date=2012-06-08 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/63bRXv6ZA?url=http://www.grammy.com/nominees |archive-date=December 1, 2011}}</ref> \"I Gotta Feeling\" ranked fifth on the ''Billboard'' Hot 100 Songs of the Decade.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/bbcom/charts/chart_display.jsp?g=Singles&f=Greece#/../../charts-decade-end/hot-100-songs?year=2009 |title=Hot 100 Decade Songs |publisher=Billboard.com |date= |accessdate=2012-06-08}}</ref> The song was also nominated as Song of the Year at the [[2009 World Music Awards]]. In March 2011, it became the first song in digital history to sell over 7 million digital copies in the United States. {{As of|June 2019}}, \"I Gotta Feeling\" has over 9 million downloads in the country, and it currently holds the record as the most downloaded song on [[iTunes]] of all time.<ref name=\"mtv.com\">{{cite web|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/articles/1631774/20100211/black_eyed_peas.jhtml |title=Black Eyed Peas, Lady Gaga Top iTunes All-Time Most-Downloaded Songs - Music, Celebrity, Artist News |publisher=MTV.com |date=2010-02-11 |accessdate=2012-06-08}}</ref> This also makes it the highest selling digital as well as non-charity single in the US ever.<ref name=\"New.music.yahoo.com\">{{cite web|url=http://new.music.yahoo.com/blogs/chart_watch/74345/week-ending-march-20-2011-songs-the-chris-brown-matter/;_ylt=AoumODvrri0gIE7HiOhd3n0PwiUv |archive-url=https://archive.is/20120713005748/http://new.music.yahoo.com/blogs/chart_watch/74345/week-ending-march-20-2011-songs-the-chris-brown-matter/;_ylt=AoumODvrri0gIE7HiOhd3n0PwiUv |url-status=dead |archive-date=July 13, 2012 |title=Week Ending March&nbsp;20, 2011: Songs: The Chris Brown Matter \u2013 Yahoo! Chart Watch |publisher=New.music.yahoo.com |date=March 23, 2011 |access-date=2011-03-24 }}</ref>\n\n\"I Gotta Feeling\" spent 14 consecutive weeks atop the ''Billboard'' Hot 100, making it the longest-running number-one single of 2009. The song was the third most successful song of the decade in Australia, as announced on January 7, 2010.<ref name=\"news.com.au\">{{cite news| url=http://www.news.com.au/adelaidenow/story/0,22606,26561471-16601,00.html | work=The Advertiser | title=Top 100 singles of the noughties | date=January 7, 2010}}</ref> Worldwide, it was the most successful song of the 21st century (with estimates putting combined sales and streams between 13 and 15 million units) until passed by \"[[Happy (Pharrell Williams song)|Happy]]\" by [[Pharrell Williams]] in 2014.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.worldmusicawards.com/index.php/news/magic-climbs-back-worlds-no1-single-week/|title=MAGIC! CLIMBS BACK TO WORLD'S NO.1 SINGLE OF THE WEEK!|date=August 23, 2014}}</ref>\n\n==Background==\n\"I Gotta Feeling\" was written and composed by all the members of [[The Black Eyed Peas]] (credited as [[will.i.am|William Adams]], [[apl.de.ap|Allan Pineda]], [[Taboo (rapper)|Jaime Gomez]], and [[Fergie (singer)|Stacy Ferguson]]) together with French producers [[David Guetta]], Fr\u00e9d\u00e9ric Riesterer (a.k.a. {{ill|Fred Rister|fr|Fred Rister}} ), both of whom produced the song. will.i.am provided additional synthesizer work to the song. The song was recorded at Square Prod in Paris, France and [[Metropolis Group|Metropolis Studios]] in London, England, United Kingdom. \"I Gotta Feeling\" is the second single released from ''[[The E.N.D]]'' (2009). [[Interscope Records]] serviced the song to [[Contemporary hit radio|contemporary hit]] and [[rhythmic crossover]] radios on June 23, 2009 in the United States.<ref name=contemporaryhit>{{cite web|title=R&R :: Going for Adds :: CHR/Top 40 |url=http://gfa.radioandrecords.com/publishGFA/GFANextPage.asp?sDate=06/15/2009&Format=1 |work=Going for Adds |publisher=[[Radio and Records|Radio & Records, Inc.]] |access-date=April 11, 2012 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120914123503/http://gfa.radioandrecords.com/publishGFA/GFANextPage.asp?sDate=06%2F15%2F2009&Format=1 |archive-date=September 14, 2012 |df= }}</ref><ref name=fmqb>{{cite web|title=Airplay Archive |url=http://www.fmqb.com/Article.asp?id=69239#29 |work=[[FMQB]] |publisher=Friday Morning Quarterback Album Report, Inc. and Mediaspan Online Services |access-date=April 11, 2012 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20091101141712/http://www.fmqb.com/Article.asp?id=69239 |archive-date=November 1, 2009}}</ref> In an interview with Annie Reuter of [[Marie Claire]], will.i.am stated that \"It's dedicated to all the party people out there in the world that want to go out and party. Mostly every song on the Black Eyed Peas record is painting a picture of our party life. It was a conscious decision to make this type of record. Times are really hard for a lot of people and you want to give them escape and you want to make them feel good about life, especially at these low points.\"<ref name=reuter>{{cite web|last=Reuter|first=Annie|title=Black Eyed Peas Talk New Album, Performing on \"American Idol\" Finale |url=http://www.marieclaire.com/world-reports/opinion/black-eyed-peas-interview|work=[[Marie Claire]]|publisher=Hearst Communications, Inc.|accessdate=April 11, 2012|date=May 19, 2009}}</ref>\n\n==Composition==\nThe song is an uptempo [[dance-pop]] song that runs a length of 4:49 (4 minutes and 49 seconds). The song follows in the inspirational dance-pop theme of ''The E.N.D'', being built upon the heavy use of [[Auto-Tune]] and futuristic synthesizers while running through a tick-tock rhythm.<ref name=bush/><ref name=balls/><ref name=lamb/> It is composed in the key of [[G major]]. The song begins in a restrained fashion then moves into a throbbing dance beat that changes patterns so that at least one reviewer thought it shifted tempos,<ref name=balls/> although in fact the tempo does not change at all, suggesting the use of a click track in recording. It contains electronic influences. The song samples a beat from the song \"Take a Dive\" by Bryan Pringle. The \"woo-hoo\" line is sampled from [[The Police]]'s song \"[[Every Breath You Take]]\". Ann Powers of ''Los Angeles Times'' noted the song's similarities to [[Five Stairsteps]]' song \"[[Ooh Child]]\", writing that it emulates the song's \"use of a repetitive, warm vocal line to signify a good mood coming on.\"<ref name=powers/> According to Jimmy Iovine of the [[Interscope Geffen A&M]] label group, the melody was inspired by the [[U2]] song \"[[I'll Go Crazy If I Don't Go Crazy Tonight]]\": \"I sent will.i.am over to the studio to do some remixes on I'll Go Crazy. He works on them for two weeks, comes back and writes I Gotta Feeling. The chords are U2 chords, 100 per cent. Will even told them.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://uk.omg.yahoo.com/news/am-borrowed-melody-u2-song-083815131.html |title=will.i.am borrowed melody from U2 song - Yahoo! omg! UK |publisher=Uk.omg.yahoo.com |date=2012-04-20 |accessdate=2012-06-08}}</ref>\n\n==Critical reception==\n\"I Gotta Feeling\" received generally positive reviews from music critics. David Balls, a writer for ''[[Digital Spy]]'', gave the song a four-star rating, writing that the song is \"every bit as quirky as its predecessor (\"[[Boom Boom Pow]]\")\".<ref name=balls/> However, he compared it to Girls Aloud's \"[[Biology (song)|Biology]]\", writing that they sound like a collection of musical ideas \"that only makes sense after a few listens.\"<ref name=balls>{{cite web|last=Balls|first=David|title=Black Eyed Peas: 'I Gotta Feeling' \u2013 Music Singles Review|url=http://www.digitalspy.com/music/singlesreviews/a164862/black-eyed-peas-i-gotta-feeling.html|work=[[Digital Spy]]|publisher=Hearst Magazines UK|accessdate=April 11, 2012}}</ref> Another writer for ''Digital Spy'', Nick Levine, praised \"I Gotta Feeling\" and \"[[Rock That Body]]\" as ace collaborations with French disc jockey [[David Guetta]].<ref name=levine>{{cite web|last=Levine|first=Nick|title=Black Eyed Peas: 'The E.N.D' \u2013 Music Album Review|url=http://www.digitalspy.com/music/albumreviews/a160073/black-eyed-peas-the-end.html|work=[[Digital Spy]]|publisher=Hearst Magazines UK|accessdate=April 11, 2012}}</ref> Music critics like John Bush of ''[[Allmusic|All Music Guide]]'' and Andy Gill of ''[[The Independent]]'' labeled it as one of the album's best tracks.<ref name=bush>{{cite web|last=Bush|first=John|title=The E.N.D (Energy Never Dies) \u2013 The Black Eyed Peas {{!}} AllMusic|url=http://www.allmusic.com/album/the-end-energy-never-dies-r1549807/review|work=[[Allmusic|All Music Guide]]|publisher=Rovi Corporation|accessdate=April 11, 2012}}</ref><ref name=gill>{{cite news|last=Gill|first=Andy|title=Album: The Black Eyed Peas, The E.N.D (Polydor) \u2013 Reviews \u2013 News|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/music/reviews/album-the-black-eyed-peas-the-end-polydor-1702917.html|work=The Independent |accessdate=April 12, 2012|location=London|date=June 12, 2009}}</ref> Ann Powers wrote a positive review about \"I Gotta Feeling\", noting that \"the Peas do let in some human sweetness and light\" on the song and that it uses \"a repetitive, warm vocal line to signify a good mood coming on.\"<ref name=powers>{{cite news|last=Powers|first=Ann|title=Album review: Black Eyed Peas' 'The E.N.D'|url=http://latimesblogs.latimes.com/music_blog/2009/06/album-review-black-eyed-peas-the-end.html|work=Los Angeles Times|accessdate=April 12, 2012|date=June 2, 2009}}</ref>\n\nBen Westhoff of ''Las Vegas Weekly'' dismissed the song as a blend of [[House music|house]], [[Electro (music)|electro]] and [[dancehall]] beats that do not work compared to songs on ''The E.N.D'' like \"[[Imma Be]]\" and \"One Tribe\".<ref name=westhoff>{{cite web|last=Westhoff|first=Ben|title=The Black Eyed Peas|url=http://www.lasvegasweekly.com/news/2009/jun/18/black-eyed-peas/|work=Las Vegas Weekly|publisher=Las Vegas Weekly|accessdate=April 12, 2012}}</ref> Mike Schiller, a writer for ''[[PopMatters]]'', found the song to be irresistible, writing that it \"is one of those dance tunes that's impossible to hate thanks to something like good natured na\u00efvet\u00e9\".<ref name=schiller>{{cite web|last=Schiller|first=Mike|title=Black Eyed Peas: The E.N.D|url=http://www.popmatters.com/pm/review/94793-black-eyed-peas-the-e.n.d|work=[[PopMatters]]|publisher=PopMatters|accessdate=April 12, 2012}}</ref> In his review of the album for ''Stuff.co.nz'', Chris Schultz dismissed the lyrics, writing that they were the worst since [[Flo Rida]]'s \"[[Right Round]]\".<ref name=schulz>{{cite web|last=Schulz|first=Chris|title=CD review: The END \u2013 Black Eyed Peas|url=http://www.stuff.co.nz/entertainment/music/album-reviews/2491594/CD-review-The-END-Black-Eyed-Peas|work=Stuff.co.nz|publisher=Fairfax New Zealand Limited|accessdate=April 12, 2012|date=June 11, 2009}}</ref>\n\n''The Observer-Dispatch'' writer David T. Farr praised the song as \"the summer track of 2009\", writing that \"It's one of those songs you grasp onto right away and crank up as the beat goes on, even the first time you hear it (guilty as charged).\"<ref name=farr>{{cite web|last=Farr |first=David T. |title=The Farr Side: Phunk doesn\u2019t E.N.D. for Black Eyed Peas |url=http://www.uticaod.com/ghs/features/x135716304/The-Farr-Side-Phunk-doesn-t-E-N-D-for-Black-Eyed-Peas |archive-url=https://archive.is/20130205084036/http://www.uticaod.com/ghs/features/x135716304/The-Farr-Side-Phunk-doesn-t-E-N-D-for-Black-Eyed-Peas |url-status=dead |archive-date=February 5, 2013 |work=The Observer-Dispatch |publisher=GateHouse Media, Inc |access-date=April 12, 2012 }}</ref> Will Hines of ''Consequence of Sound'' shared similar feelings about \"I Gotta Feeling\", defining it as \"chart baiting\".<ref name=hines>{{cite web|last=Hines|first=Will|title=Album Review: Black Eyed Peas \u2013 The E.N.D|url=http://consequenceofsound.net/2009/06/album-review-black-eyed-peas-the-end/|work=Consequence of Sound|publisher=Consequence of Sound|accessdate=April 12, 2012}}</ref> Guy Blackman, a writer for ''[[The Age]]'', labeled \"I Gotta Feeling\" and \"Boom Boom Pow\" as further dumbed-down dance-pop songs.<ref name=blackman>{{cite news|last=Blackman|first=Guy|title=The E.N.D|url=http://www.theage.com.au/news/entertainment/music/cd-reviews/the-end/2009/06/18/1244918135166.html|work=The Age |location=Australia|publisher=Fairfax Digital|accessdate=April 12, 2012|date=June 23, 2009}}</ref> Bill Lamb of ''[[About.com]]'' gave the song a four-star rating, praising it for the difference of style from previous releases by The Black Eyed Peas and as a great summer song with a feel good mood., but he criticized the lack of lyrical depth and constant use of Auto-Tune.<ref name=lamb>{{cite web|last=Lamb|first=Bill|title=Black Eyed Peas \u2013 \"I Gotta Feelin'\"|url=http://top40.about.com/od/singles/gr/igottafeelin.htm|work=[[About.com]]|publisher=[[The New York Times Company]]|access-date=April 12, 2012|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120508052908/http://top40.about.com/od/singles/gr/igottafeelin.htm|archive-date=May 8, 2012}}</ref> ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'''s Chris Williams praised the song as their most mainstream release, writing that \"they trade off on a simple, yet effective melody and message\".<ref name=williams>{{cite journal|url=https://books.google.com/books?rview=1&id=3nN5lr7UanQC&q=i+gotta+feeling#v=snippet&q=i%20gotta%20feeling&f=false|title=Billboard Reviews \u2013 Singles|journal=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|date=June 2009|volume=121|issue=23|page=52|issn=0006-2510|accessdate=April 13, 2012}}</ref>\n\n==Chart performance==\n\"I Gotta Feeling\" followed in the international success of ''[[The E.N.D]]'''s lead single \"[[Boom Boom Pow]]\". In the United States, the song debuted on the [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]] at number two, behind \"Boom Boom Pow\", prompted by sales of 249,000 downloads.<ref>{{cite web|last=Ben-Yehuda|first=Ayala|title=Black Eyed Peas Take Top Two Slots On Billboard Hot 100|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/268343/black-eyed-peas-take-top-two-slots-on-billboard-hot-100|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|accessdate=April 13, 2012}}</ref> The song held at number two for another week before rising to the top position on the chart.<ref>{{cite web|title='Feeling' is No. 1 on U.S. record chart |url=http://www.upi.com/Entertainment_News/2009/07/09/Feeling-is-No-1-on-US-record-chart/UPI-49711247180220/|work=UPI|publisher=United Press International, Inc.|accessdate=April 13, 2012|date=July 9, 2009}}</ref> On July 30, 2009, it was reported that the song, along with \"Boom Boom Pow\" helped earn The Black Eyed Peas the longest run at number one on the ''Billboard'' Hot 100 by a duo or group (17 weeks).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/267898/black-eyed-peas-set-billboard-hot-100-record|title=Black Eyed Peas Set Billboard Hot 100 Record|last=Ben-Yehuda|first=Ayala|last2=Caulfield|first2=Keith|date=July 30, 2009|website=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|archive-url=|archive-date=|url-status=|access-date=April 13, 2012|last3=Pietroluongo|first3=Silvio}}</ref> The song stayed at number one on the chart for a total of fourteen weeks before being unseated by [[Jay Sean]]'s \"[[Down (Jay Sean song)|Down]]\".<ref name=pietroluongo>{{cite web|last=Pietroluongo|first=Silvio|title=Jay Sean Sends Peas Packing From Hot 100 Penthouse|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/267156/jay-sean-sends-peas-packing-from-hot-100-penthouse|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|accessdate=April 13, 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Hot 100 \u2013 October 17, 2009|url=http://www.billboard.com/charts/2009-10-17/hot-100|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|accessdate=April 13, 2012}}</ref> The song, together with \"Boom Boom Pow\", earned the group a total of 26 consecutive weeks atop the Hot 100 chart while also earning them their longest running single on the chart, with a total of 56 weeks logged.<ref name=pietroluongo/><ref name=billboardcharts/>\n\n\"I Gotta Feeling\" also peaked at number one on several other ''Billboard'' charts, including [[Hot Digital Songs]], [[Mainstream Top 40]], and [[Radio Songs]].<ref name=billboardcharts>{{cite web|title=I Gotta Feeling \u2013 Billboard Chart History|url={{BillboardURLbyName|artist=the black eyed peas|chart=all}}|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|accessdate=April 13, 2012}}</ref> It was the group's second single to sell over 6 million downloads in the United States, and was certified 7\u00d7 Platinum on August 25, 2010 by the [[Recording Industry Association of America]] (RIAA) signifying sales of over 7 million units. It was the first song to reach sales of over 6 million (July 25, 2010), 7 million (March 20, 2011), 8 million (June 24, 2012), and 9 million (June 7, 2019).<ref name=\"yahoo_may2013\">{{cite news|url=http://music.yahoo.com/blogs/chart-watch/chart-watch-extra-itunes-turns-10-213705272.html|title=Chart Watch Extra: iTunes Turns 10|last=Grein|first=Paul|date=May 1, 2013|work=Yahoo Music (Chart Watch)|accessdate=May 4, 2013}}</ref><ref>https://twitter.com/HITSDD/status/1137046191378579456</ref> It also earned the accolade of being the best digital seller in history.<ref name=\"mtv.com\"/>\n\nIn Canada, the song debuted on the [[Canadian Hot 100]] at number two behind \"Boom Boom Pow\", similar to its beginning run in the United States, on the week ending June 27, 2009.<ref>{{cite web|title=Canadian Hot 100 \u2013 June 27, 2009|url=http://www.billboard.com/charts/2009-06-27/canadian-hot-100|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|accessdate=April 13, 2012}}</ref> The next week, it rose to number one following a surge in airplay, where it maintained that position for 16 consecutive weeks, setting the record for longest run at number one since the chart's inception in 2007.<ref>{{cite web|title=Canadian Hot 100 \u2013 July 4, 2009|url=http://www.billboard.com/charts/2009-07-04/canadian-hot-100|work=Billboard|accessdate=April 13, 2012}}</ref><ref name=internationalchartsigf>{{cite web|title=The Black Eyed Peas \u2013 I Gotta Feeling|url=http://acharts.us/song/44000|work=aCharts|publisher=acharts.us|accessdate=April 13, 2012}}</ref> The song was present on the chart for a total of 76 weeks, setting the record for longest stay on the chart.<ref name=billboardcharts/><ref name=internationalchartsigf/> The song was certified Diamond by Music Canada for sales of over 800,000 digital downloads.<ref name=\"Canada Certified Diamond\">{{cite web|title=Gold Platinum Database|url=https://musiccanada.com/GPSearchResult.aspx?st=I%20Gotta%20Feeling&ica=False&sa=Black%20Eyed%20Peas&sl=&smt=0&sat=-1&ssd=5/1/2007&ssb=Artist|work=[[Music Canada]]|accessdate=April 16, 2012}}</ref>\n\n\"I Gotta Feeling\" fared similarly in international markets. The song had a slower rise in the United Kingdom, where it debuted at number 70 on the week ending June 20, 2009.<ref>{{cite web|title=UK Singles Top 75 \u2013 June 20, 2009|url=http://acharts.us/uk_singles_top_75/2009/25|work=aCharts|publisher=acharts.us|accessdate=April 16, 2012}}</ref> It quickly picked up momentum, moving into the top five in its fifth week on the chart. On the week ending August 8, 2009, the song peaked at number one, where it stayed for two non-consecutive weeks.<ref>{{cite web|title=2009 Top 40 Official UK Singles Archive \u2013 August 8, 2009|url=http://www.officialcharts.com/archive-chart/_/1/2009-08-08/|work=[[Official Chart Company]]|accessdate=April 16, 2012|date=August 8, 2009}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=2009 Top 40 Official UK Singles Archive \u2013 August 22, 2009|url=http://www.officialcharts.com/archive-chart/_/1/2009-08-22/|work=[[Official Chart Company]]|accessdate=April 16, 2012|date=August 8, 2009}}</ref> \"I Gotta Feeling\" held within the top ten for 16 consecutive weeks and lasted on the chart for a total of 76 weeks. The song was certified Platinum by the [[British Phonographic Industry]] on January 7, 2010 for sales of 600,000 units.<ref>{{cite web|title=British single certifications \u2013 Black Eyed Peas \u2013 I Gotta Feeling |url=http://www.bpi.co.uk/certifiedawards/search.aspx |work=British Phonographic Industry |access-date=April 16, 2012 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/6DaMNbmDo?url=http://www.bpi.co.uk/certifiedawards/search.aspx |archive-date=January 11, 2013}}</ref> \"I Gotta Feeling\" became the first song to sell over one million units based solely on the strength of digital downloads,<ref>{{cite web|last=Kaufman|first=Gil|title=Adele, Lady Gaga, Justin Bieber Land New Guinness Records|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/articles/1670701/lady-gaga-adele-guinness-book-of-world-records.jhtml|publisher=MTV News|accessdate=April 13, 2012|date=September 14, 2011}}</ref> and has sold over 1.44 million copies in the United Kingdom as of May 2014.<ref name=\"UK sales\">{{cite web|url=https://www.officialcharts.com/chart-news/official-charts-flashback-2009-black-eyed-peas-boom-boom-pow__4785/|title=Official Charts Flashback 2009: Black Eyed Peas \u2013 Boom Boom Pow|last=Myers|first=Justin|date=23 May 2014|publisher=[[Official Charts Company]]|accessdate=15 December 2019}}</ref> In Ireland, the song peaked at number one and held that position for 12 non-consecutive weeks, falling to number two on the week of August 27, 2009 after six weeks in the top position.<ref name=internationalchartsigf/><ref>{{cite web|title=TOP 50 SINGLES, WEEK ENDING 27 August 2009|url=http://www.chart-track.co.uk/index.jsp?c=p%2Fmusicvideo%2Fmusic%2Farchive%2Findex_test.jsp&ct=240001&arch=t&lyr=2009&year=2009&week=35|work=[[Irish Singles Chart]]|publisher=GFK Chart-Track|accessdate=April 16, 2012}}</ref> It rose to number one the following week and held that position for another six weeks.<ref name=internationalchartsigf/> In Sweden, the song debuted on the chart at number 36 on the week ending July 19, 2009.<ref name=Switzerland/> It quickly entered the top ten and peaked at number one in its seventh week on the chart.<ref name=Switzerland/> \"I Gotta Feeling\" maintained its position there for eight consecutive weeks and stayed present on the charts for a total of 87 weeks.<ref name=Switzerland>{{cite web|title=The Black Eyed Peas \u2013 I Gotta Feeling|url=http://www.swisscharts.com/showitem.asp?interpret=The+Black+Eyed+Peas&titel=I+Gotta+Feeling&cat=s|work=swisscharts.com|publisher=Hung Medien|accessdate=April 16, 2012}}</ref> The single was certified double platinum for sales of 40,000 units.<ref name=\"Switzerland Certification\">{{cite web|title=The Official Swiss Charts and Music Community |url=http://swisscharts.com/awards.asp?year=2010 |work=swisscharts.com |publisher=Hung Medien |access-date=April 16, 2012 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100526021757/http://swisscharts.com/awards.asp?year=2010 |archive-date=May 26, 2010}}</ref> In Germany, the song debuted on the chart at number seven and rose to number three two weeks later.<ref name=Germany>{{cite web|title=Black Eyed Peas - I Gotta Feeling @ Top40-Charts.com|url=http://top40-charts.com/songs/full.php?sid=26882&sort=chartid|work=Top40-Charts.com|publisher=top40-charts.com|accessdate=April 16, 2012}}</ref>\n\n\"I Gotta Feeling\" peaked at number one in countries including Australia, Austria, Belgium, Denmark, Italy, The Netherlands, and New Zealand.<ref name=internationalchartsigf/> The song reached top five peak positions in Finland, France, Norway, and Spain.<ref name=internationalchartsigf/> It has sold over seven million units worldwide in 2009 and an additional six million in 2010, as reported by the IFPI.<ref name=ifpione>{{cite web|title=Digital Music Sales Around the World|url=http://www.ifpi.com/content/library/dmr2010.pdf|work=[[International Federation of the Phonographic Industry]]|publisher=IFPI|accessdate=April 13, 2012|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120322183800/http://www.ifpi.com/content/library/dmr2010.pdf|archive-date=March 22, 2012|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref name=ifpitwo>{{cite web|title=IFPI publishes Digital Music Report 2011|url=http://www.ifpi.com/content/section_resources/dmr2011.html|work=[[International Federation of the Phonographic Industry]]|publisher=IFPI|accessdate=April 13, 2012|archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/636Sb7TCl?url=http://www.ifpi.com/content/section_resources/dmr2011.html|archive-date=November 11, 2011|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\n==Live performance==\nOn September 8, 2009, the song was performed (with slight modification) by The Black Eyed Peas for the taping of the Kick-off Party for the 24th season of ''[[The Oprah Winfrey Show]]'', with 21,000 fans performing a dance on the \"[[Magnificent Mile]]\" portion of [[Michigan Avenue (Chicago)|Michigan Avenue]] in Chicago, Illinois.<ref>[http://www.oprah.com/article/oprahshow/20090908-tows-flash-mob-dance Oprah's Kickoff Party Dance] Oprah.com</ref> They also performed the song at the [[52nd Grammy Awards]] nomination announcement ceremony with [[David Guetta]] (a remix edit by David Guetta appears on his album, [[One Love (David Guetta album)|''One Love'']]). The Black Eyed Peas also performed the song during a concert at [[Mont Kiara]], [[Kuala Lumpur]], Malaysia in 2009. Being the headliners of the [[Super Bowl XLV halftime show]], The Black Eyed Peas sang \"I Gotta Feeling\" in front of more than 100,000 fans at [[Cowboys Stadium]]. On April 29, 2011, they performed the song along with others at the \"i.am.FIRST\" event at the [[FIRST Robotics Competition]] World Championships. For [[Queen Elizabeth II]]'s [[Diamond Jubilee Concert]], will.i.am and [[Jessie J]] sang a duet of \"I Gotta Feeling\".<ref>{{cite news|last=Victoria|first=Ward|title=Diamond Jubilee: Queen giggles as she meets stars of show backstage|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/uknews/the_queens_diamond_jubilee/9312546/Diamond-Jubilee-Queen-giggles-as-she-meets-stars-of-show-backstage.html|work=[[The Daily Telegraph]]|publisher=[[Telegraph Media Group]]|date=6 June 2012|accessdate=6 June 2012|location=London}}</ref> At the last part of the [[2019 Southeast Asian Games]] [[2019 Southeast Asian Games closing ceremony|closing ceremony]] at the [[New Clark City Athletics Stadium]] in the [[Philippines]], this song was performed again, except that [[Fergie (singer)|Fergie]]'s part was sung by J Rey Soul (stage name of Jessica Reynoso), whom [[apl.de.ap]] introduced to the audience.\n\n==Music video==\n[[File:I Gotta Feeling (Black Eyed Peas music video - screenshot).jpg|200px|thumb|right|A party scene showing (from left to right) [[Apl.de.ap]], [[Fergie (singer)|Fergie]], [[will.i.am]] and [[Taboo (rapper)|Taboo]] in the official music video for \"I Gotta Feeling\".]]\nThe official final version was released on June 2 on Dipdive and on June 15 on [[iTunes]]. There is both a censored version and an explicit version of the music video and a live performance of the explicit video. The video starts with scenes in [[Hollywood Blvd.]] and then showing [[will.i.am]] combing his hair and [[Fergie (singer)|Fergie]] putting on make-up while wearing lingerie. It also shows [[Taboo (rapper)|Taboo]] checking his messages on [[Dipdive]] and [[apl.de.ap]] checking his text messages. Then it cuts to the party as the first verse starts. The video ends with a large sign with human-sized letters that reads \"The E.N.D\" The video is directed by Mikey Mee of ''Little Minx'' and features guest appearances by [[Katy Perry]], [[David Guetta]], [[Kid Cudi]], members of the [[indie rock]] band [[Gossip (band)|Gossip]], the designer duo [[Dean and Dan Caten]] of Dsquared<sup>2</sup> and ''[[RuPaul's Drag Race]]'' alumni [[Ongina (drag queen)|Ongina]].\n\n==Credits and personnel==\nCredits adapted from the liner notes of ''The E.N.D'', [[Interscope Records]], in association with [[will.i.am Music Group]].<ref name=\"Notes\">{{cite AV media notes|others=[[The Black Eyed Peas]]|title=[[The E.N.D]]|year=2009|type= inlay cover|publisher= [[Interscope Records]], [[will.i.am Music Group]]}}</ref>\n\n;Recording and mixing\n* Recorded at Square Prod in Paris, France and [[Metropolis Group|Metropolis Studios]] in London, England, United Kingdom.\n* Mixed by Dylan \"3-D\" Dresdow at Paper V.U. Studios and [[Record Plant]] in Los Angeles, CA, USA.\n\n;Personnel\n* Songwriting \u2013 [[will.i.am]], [[apl.de.ap]], [[Taboo (rapper)|Taboo]], [[Fergie (singer)|Fergie]], [[David Guetta]], Frederick Riesterer\n* Vocals - will.i.am, apl.de.ap, Taboo, Fergie\n* Production \u2013 David Guetta, Frederick Riesterer\n* Synths \u2013 will.i.am\n\n==Track listing==\n* '''Digital download (worldwide version)'''\n# \"I Gotta Feeling\" \u2013 4:49\n\n* '''UK CD Single'''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.discogs.com/Black-Eyed-Peas-The-I-Gotta-Feeling/release/1896104|title=The Black Eyed Peas \u2013 I Gotta Feeling|publisher=Discogs.com |accessdate=2009-12-27}}</ref>\n# \"I Gotta Feeling\" <small>(Radio Edit)</small> \u2013 4:06\n# \"Boom Boom Pow\" <small>(David Guetta's Electro Hop Remix)</small> \u2013 4:05\n\n* '''German CD Single'''\n# \"I Gotta F